-- ============================================================================
-- BACKGROUND
-- ============================================================================
--
-- session_2026-05-15a-governance-reconciliation surfaced 17 BROKEN_CON_ID
-- failures in scripts/validate_cross_refs.py after the validator's
-- references/search-logs/ → references/search-log/ path drift was fixed and
-- the validator stopped failing fast on false-positive MISSING_SEARCH_LOGs.
--
-- Investigation traced the issue:
--
--   2026-05-06 14:05 (commit 3254705c): synthesis-scan added CON-0253..CON-0274
--   to the connections table (22 connections; commit message says so).
--   Combined with earlier CON-0247..CON-0252 (added 2026-05-05 connection-
--   discovery session), the connections table at commit 3254705c held 273
--   rows with max=CON-0274.
--
--   2026-05-07 21:43 (commit 412739f7): "decision-capture: init tracking DB +
--   migrations 001-005 + 86 items populated". The DB was re-initialised and
--   connections were lost (count=0 immediately after this commit).
--
--   Subsequent connection migrations restored CON-0001..CON-0246 from a
--   pre-2026-05-06 snapshot. CON-0247..CON-0274 were not in that snapshot
--   and were never re-migrated. State persisted through:
--     - 2026-05-13 20:38 (commit d717bfae): DB has 245 connections, max CON-0246
--     - 2026-05-15 16:19 (commit d5449e8f): baseline 012 captured the
--       245-connection state as the new starting line (per DR-2026-05-15
--       Option B). CON-0247..0274 are now lost from the migration history.
--     - 2026-05-15 16:31 (commit d36f55b3): v1_legacy sync; connections
--       unchanged at 245.
--
-- Twenty-eight markdown references to the lost connections remained in place,
-- creating a structural-validation failure but more importantly losing
-- substantive content. Example: CON-0264 documents the RT60 ≤0.4s
-- multi-population convergence across DEAF, NDV/AUT, MH, PAIN, OFS — referenced
-- in parts/v10/part04.md as "Universal acoustic target [CON-0264]". This is a
-- five-population convergence finding that the BPC rewrite workplan depends on.
--
-- This is the caller-sweep miss that architecture v2.3 <migration_and_growth>
-- "Removing or renaming structural elements" was authored to prevent. The
-- 2026-05-07 DB reset succeeded mechanically but left orphan markdown
-- references that a caller-sweep would have caught.
--
-- ============================================================================
-- RESTORATION SOURCE
-- ============================================================================
--
-- Source of truth: data/guidebook.db at git SHA 3254705c (2026-05-06 14:05).
